config PANICOS_DEVICE_RG35XX_PRO_LPDDR3
	bool "anbernic/rg35xx-pro-lpddr3 (Allwinner H700, LPDDR3 variant)"
	select PANICOS_SOC_ALLWINNER_H700
	help
	  Anbernic RG35XX Pro — LPDDR3 DRAM variant (less common; some
	  early or budget units). U-Boot uses
	  anbernic_rg35xx_h700_lpddr3_defconfig with DCDC3 = 1200 mV and
	  LPDDR3-specific DRAM timings.

	  For the more common LPDDR4 retail variant, build the
	  "rg35xx-pro" target instead. Flashing the wrong DRAM-variant
	  image WILL cause boot failure — they share kernel, DTBs, and
	  rootfs but the U-Boot SPL is built differently.

	  Kernel: Linux 7.0.1 mainline + ROCKNIX patches.
